26:34.994 --> 26:38.128
Then what is?

26:43.703 --> 26:47.938
I am going to burn this
hospital gown when i get home.

26:47.940 --> 26:49.306
Who could possibly look good
in this?

26:49.308 --> 26:51.241
Oh, i could.

26:51.243 --> 26:52.610
What? I could.

26:52.612 --> 26:54.712
[ chuckles ]

26:54.714 --> 26:56.347
It's so nice
to be on my feet again.

26:56.349 --> 26:58.082
I can't wait
to get back to work.

26:58.084 --> 26:59.283
Well, don't ask marisol
to find you a job.

26:59.285 --> 27:00.784
She takes forever.

27:00.786 --> 27:03.153
Oh, she already set up
some interviews for me.

27:03.155 --> 27:04.755
What?

27:04.757 --> 27:06.056
Well, i told her
that i couldn't start

27:06.058 --> 27:07.224
For a couple of weeks,

27:07.226 --> 27:10.127
But she was so excited
to help me.

27:10.129 --> 27:12.730
You were in a coma!
You can barely walk!

27:12.732 --> 27:14.398
You're scaring me.

27:14.400 --> 27:15.966
Why wouldn't she find me
a job?

27:15.968 --> 27:17.368
I'm her friend, too.

27:17.370 --> 27:20.404
Mm. She's probably just
looking for the perfect fit.

27:20.406 --> 27:22.806
Or maybe
she's just full of it.

27:24.410 --> 27:26.310
[ alarm beeping ]
what -- what are you doing?

27:26.312 --> 27:27.645
This is an emergency.

27:27.647 --> 27:29.813
Rosie, are you okay?

27:29.815 --> 27:32.816
Yeah, yeah, yeah, she's fine.
I need you to do me a favor.

27:35.955 --> 27:39.123
[ cellphone rings ]

27:39.125 --> 27:40.257
This is marisol.

27:40.259 --> 27:41.358
Jerry: Good day.

27:41.360 --> 27:43.661
This is...

27:43.663 --> 27:45.229
Thurston howell iii.

27:45.231 --> 27:47.698
Why do i know
that name?

27:47.700 --> 27:49.066
I'm a very rich
millionaire.

27:49.068 --> 27:50.100
Good.

27:50.102 --> 27:51.268
Congratulations.

27:51.270 --> 27:52.670
Thank you.

27:52.672 --> 27:54.171
Now, i'm in dire need
of a maid.

27:54.173 --> 27:55.439
Oh.

27:55.441 --> 27:57.207
Well, then you've called
the right place.

27:57.209 --> 27:58.842
Can you tell me a little bit
about what you're looking for?

27:58.844 --> 28:01.245
What am i looking for?
Fabulous question.

28:02.148 --> 28:04.348
You want someone
who can start today.

28:04.350 --> 28:05.783
She should be able
to start today.

28:05.785 --> 28:08.185
Stop this!
Marisol is your friend.

28:08.187 --> 28:10.220
And you love
puerto ricans.

28:10.222 --> 28:11.755
Say it!

28:11.757 --> 28:13.457
And i love puerto ricans...
For some reason.

28:13.459 --> 28:17.995
Uh...Well, i have someone
who is very eager,

28:17.997 --> 28:19.396
And i think she'd be
an excellent match.

28:19.398 --> 28:20.731
She has someone.

28:20.733 --> 28:22.199
Her name is
ruth rodriguez.

28:22.201 --> 28:23.867
Ruth rodriguez.

28:23.869 --> 28:26.470
So, i just need
your address --
hell no!

28:26.472 --> 28:28.238
[ beep ]
sir?

28:28.240 --> 28:31.075
Hello?

28:31.077 --> 28:33.210
[ beep ]

28:38.818 --> 28:40.084
Do you have a minute?

28:40.086 --> 28:43.020
I do.

28:45.458 --> 28:48.225
What's that?

28:48.227 --> 28:51.128
It's my
<i>Ã¡ngel de la guardia</i> pendant.

28:51.130 --> 28:55.265
The one
your dad gave you.

28:55.267 --> 28:57.801
I want the baby
to have it.

28:57.803 --> 29:00.170
For good luck.

29:00.172 --> 29:03.373
That's really sweet.

29:03.375 --> 29:07.978
Look, i think i got so upset
because...

29:07.980 --> 29:11.949
It feels like you're starting
a new family without me.

29:11.951 --> 29:14.752
And it really hurt.

29:14.754 --> 29:17.454
I can understand that.

29:19.391 --> 29:21.859
You're starting
a new life with remi.

29:21.861 --> 29:23.460
Without me.

29:23.462 --> 29:26.263
And that hurts, too.

29:26.265 --> 29:31.368
<i>Mami,</i>
i'm so sorry i overreacted.

29:31.370 --> 29:34.438
You're my daughter.
Of course you overreacted.

29:34.440 --> 29:35.773
It's what we do.

29:35.775 --> 29:37.307
[ chuckles ]

29:37.309 --> 29:39.309
We don't have to get married
if you don't want us to.

29:39.311 --> 29:40.878
Oh...

29:40.880 --> 29:44.214
That's not up to me anymore.
You're a grownup now.

29:45.885 --> 29:48.452
But i love you
no matter what.

29:48.454 --> 29:50.087
[ sighs ]

29:50.089 --> 29:51.922
I love you, too,<i> mami.</i>

29:51.924 --> 29:55.058
I'm gonna miss you
so much.

29:55.060 --> 29:57.961
Me too.

29:57.963 --> 30:00.164
Ruth rodriguez?

30:01.066 --> 30:02.299
Ruth rodriguez?!

30:02.301 --> 30:04.835
Oh, my god. That phone call.
That was you?

30:04.837 --> 30:06.236
You were supposed
to give <i> me</i> that job.

30:06.238 --> 30:08.305
Me! Carmen luna!

30:08.307 --> 30:10.140
So you were testing me?

30:10.142 --> 30:11.575
Yes. And you failed.

30:13.345 --> 30:15.312
I thought
you were my friend.

30:15.314 --> 30:16.413
Um...

30:16.415 --> 30:17.948
I'm letting you live here.

30:17.950 --> 30:20.050
I'm feeding you.
Of course i'm your friend.

30:20.052 --> 30:22.352
Then why is it such a big deal
to find me a job?

30:22.354 --> 30:24.354
Because
you're a bad maid!

30:24.356 --> 30:26.256
So, what?

30:26.258 --> 30:28.525
You're not even
gonna deny it?

30:28.527 --> 30:30.093
Why would i deny it?

30:30.095 --> 30:32.162
It's not like you think
i'm a bad singer.

30:32.164 --> 30:34.598
This is the problem.
You don't care.

30:34.600 --> 30:37.301
Who cares about
being a good maid?

30:37.303 --> 30:41.271
A lot of people!
Zoila, rosie.

30:41.273 --> 30:44.308
Well, how is it any
of your business if i'm good?

30:44.310 --> 30:46.310
Carmen!

30:46.312 --> 30:49.279
This is a placement agency.
It is literally my business.

30:49.281 --> 30:51.315
Oh.

30:51.317 --> 30:53.317
Businesses are built
on reputations.

30:53.319 --> 30:56.887
If you're bad,
it reflects on <i> me.</i>

30:56.889 --> 30:58.422
I guess.
[ sighs ]

30:58.424 --> 31:02.359
Carmen, you're a diva,
and we love that,

31:02.361 --> 31:04.228
But it can't always
be about you.

31:06.866 --> 31:08.298
Okay.

31:09.335 --> 31:11.335
You don't have to find me a job.
I get it.

31:11.337 --> 31:13.303
Really?

31:13.305 --> 31:15.339
I'm proud of you for starting
this business, marisol,

31:15.341 --> 31:17.107
And i don't want mess it up
for you, okay?

31:17.109 --> 31:19.376
So, i'll find something
on my own.

31:19.378 --> 31:21.211
I'm sure you will.

31:21.213 --> 31:25.015
Until then,
i'll just keep crashing here.

31:33.459 --> 31:35.392
I'm so proud of you
for giving this a chance.

31:35.394 --> 31:38.028
"proud" is no longer a word
in my vocabulary.

31:38.030 --> 31:39.496
What are you doing?

31:39.498 --> 31:42.165
I don't want anyone to see me
in this godforsaken place.

31:42.167 --> 31:45.135
Well, sweetheart, everyone's
come here for the same purpose.

31:45.137 --> 31:46.403
There's no shame here.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.572
[ sighs ] fine.

31:48.574 --> 31:50.440
Let's just get this
over with.

31:50.442 --> 31:52.609
That's the spirit.

31:55.948 --> 31:57.447
[ gasps ]

31:57.449 --> 31:59.116
[ slaps ]

31:59.118 --> 32:00.984
Ahh.

32:00.986 --> 32:03.921
Evelyn: Why, that looks
horribly uncomfortable.

32:03.923 --> 32:06.123
Yes. Lucky devil.

32:06.125 --> 32:07.991
What strikes your fancy,
darling?

32:07.993 --> 32:09.693
Uh, handcuffs?

32:09.695 --> 32:12.429
Whips? Ball gag?

32:12.431 --> 32:15.032
Oh, a riding crop.

32:15.034 --> 32:18.135
As a girl i used to adore
my equestrian lessons.

32:18.137 --> 32:19.169
You know
how to use that?

32:19.171 --> 32:20.203
On a horse.

32:20.205 --> 32:22.105
[ neighs ]

32:23.175 --> 32:24.675
[ nickers ]

32:24.677 --> 32:31.214
Well, perhaps
if we found a private room...

32:31.216 --> 32:33.417
Evelyn powell?

32:35.054 --> 32:38.155
It's me. Mitzy.
From the historical society?

32:38.157 --> 32:40.223
Oh, god...

32:40.225 --> 32:42.292
Relax. She's here, too. There's
no reason to be embarrassed.

32:44.530 --> 32:45.629
Hello, mitzy.

32:45.631 --> 32:47.731
What's this i hear
about a leg?

32:49.101 --> 32:51.234
What are you people doing
in that house?

33:00.746 --> 33:03.981
I'm so glad
you stopped by.

33:03.983 --> 33:05.349
How is it working
with the stappords?

33:05.351 --> 33:06.717
Well...

33:06.719 --> 33:08.552
'cause it was such a joy
helping you get that job.

33:08.554 --> 33:09.619
I'm sure
you're loving it.

33:09.621 --> 33:11.455
I had to quit.

33:11.457 --> 33:13.256
What?
I'm sorry.

33:13.258 --> 33:14.491
Can you help me
find something else?

33:14.493 --> 33:16.093
Wait, what happened?

33:16.095 --> 33:20.464
Well, mrs. Stappord
was asking, uh, a lot of me.

33:20.466 --> 33:21.565
Really?

33:21.567 --> 33:23.500
I didn't have
that experience.

33:23.502 --> 33:26.503
No.
No, i'm sure you didn't.

33:26.505 --> 33:29.439
Well, i'm sure that
this is just a misunderstanding.

33:29.441 --> 33:31.008
I'll just call her.

33:31.010 --> 33:34.011
No. I don't want this to be
a whole thing.

33:34.013 --> 33:35.512
I really just want
to move on.

33:35.514 --> 33:37.514
Without even trying
to fix the problem?

33:37.516 --> 33:40.283
I don't think
it can be fixed.

33:40.285 --> 33:43.186
I'm sorry.

33:43.188 --> 33:45.055
Blanca,
can i offer you some advice?

33:45.057 --> 33:46.523
Mm-hmm.

33:46.525 --> 33:50.427
When an employer asks
a lot of you,

33:50.429 --> 33:52.095
You're allowed to ask
for something in return.

33:52.097 --> 33:53.530
I am?

33:53.532 --> 33:58.769
Sometimes a problem is
just an opportunity in disguise.

34:06.545 --> 34:10.380
Hey, babe.
What's up?

34:10.382 --> 34:12.815
We don't have to get married
right away.

34:12.818 --> 34:14.150
What?

34:14.152 --> 34:15.585
We can just be engaged,

34:15.587 --> 34:18.522
And maybe in a year
we can plan a big wedding

34:18.524 --> 34:19.790
And have
our families there.

34:19.792 --> 34:22.659
[ sighs ]

34:22.661 --> 34:24.061
That sounds
really nice.

34:24.063 --> 34:27.230
So...
You don't mind waiting?

34:27.232 --> 34:30.300
Of course not.
Anything for you.

34:31.737 --> 34:34.471
Though i'm not gonna lie,
there was one thing

34:34.473 --> 34:38.641
I was really, really
looking forward to.

34:38.643 --> 34:43.580
Well, maybe we don't have to
wait for everything.

34:50.621 --> 34:51.788
Oh, thank god.

35:03.335 --> 35:06.236
Taylor:
...Told me not to worry.

35:06.238 --> 35:08.738
You said you would
take care of everything.

35:08.740 --> 35:10.874
Okay, then why were the police
over there asking about that...

35:10.876 --> 35:12.576
Well, i mean --

35:15.447 --> 35:20.117
Uh, i will, uh, call you back.
I got to go.

35:20.119 --> 35:23.487
Blanca, come in.

35:23.489 --> 35:26.156
Hi. I'm sorry.
Am i interrupting something?

35:26.158 --> 35:27.724
Uh...
[ door closes ]

35:27.726 --> 35:30.527
Uh, no.
It was, um...Michael.

35:30.529 --> 35:31.728
[ chuckles ]

35:31.730 --> 35:33.530
He's extending
his business trip.

35:33.532 --> 35:34.631
Oh.

35:34.633 --> 35:38.168
So,
what can i do for you?

35:38.170 --> 35:41.805
My mom was a maid.

35:41.807 --> 35:43.840
What?

35:43.842 --> 35:48.612
Yeah, she cleaned houses
so that i wouldn't have to.

35:48.614 --> 35:51.214
And before she died, she made me
promise to go to college

35:51.216 --> 35:52.616
And make something
of my life.

35:52.618 --> 35:56.620
She sounds like
a good mom.

35:56.622 --> 35:58.455
She was.

35:58.457 --> 36:01.691
And, yeah,
i'm trying to keep my promise.

36:01.693 --> 36:05.262
But it's hard.
College costs so much money.

36:05.264 --> 36:09.699
There's books and classes
and enrollment fees...

36:09.701 --> 36:12.469
I wish i had
a scholarship.

36:12.471 --> 36:13.703
But i don't.

36:13.705 --> 36:17.641
Oh.

36:17.643 --> 36:20.310
Well, maybe
if you came back to work here,

36:20.312 --> 36:21.912
I could give you
a raise.

36:21.914 --> 36:25.415
It'd have to be
a pretty big raise.

36:25.417 --> 36:29.486
It would be.

36:29.488 --> 36:30.954
You'd be able
to pay your tuition,

36:30.956 --> 36:33.924
Finish college,
make your mom proud.

36:33.926 --> 36:37.594
Well, i would be so grateful
for that.

36:37.596 --> 36:40.597
Really,
i'd be grateful and...

36:40.599 --> 36:42.599
Quiet.

36:45.537 --> 36:49.573
I'll get my checkbook.

37:01.553 --> 37:03.353
Mr. Powell?

37:03.355 --> 37:05.222
Can i talk to you?

37:05.224 --> 37:08.692
Well, since evelyn isn't,
i suppose <i> someone</i> should.

37:09.962 --> 37:11.328
How can i help you?

37:11.330 --> 37:12.562
I have good news.

37:12.564 --> 37:14.898
And some
not-so-good news.

37:14.900 --> 37:15.999
[ sighs ]

37:17.936 --> 37:19.803
[ cellphone rings ]

37:19.805 --> 37:23.240
Hello?

37:23.242 --> 37:24.474
Marisol,
thank god i caught you.

37:24.476 --> 37:26.243
Adrian.
I need a maid.

37:26.245 --> 37:27.711
Well, what happened
to valentina?

37:27.713 --> 37:29.446
She got engaged.

37:29.448 --> 37:31.514
Oh, that's wonderful!

37:31.516 --> 37:33.016
It's a catastrophe!

37:33.018 --> 37:34.618
She's abandoning us
at the worst possible moment.

37:34.620 --> 37:35.919
She is?

37:35.921 --> 37:37.320
Oh, evelyn is already furious at
me.

37:37.322 --> 37:38.388
This is the last thing
she needs.

37:38.390 --> 37:40.290
Y-you have to help.

37:40.292 --> 37:41.791
Well, i'm not sure
i have someone

37:41.793 --> 37:43.593
Who is up to
evelyn's high standards.

37:43.595 --> 37:45.929
Honestly, evelyn loves
yelling at bad maids.

37:45.931 --> 37:47.297
She finds it soothing.

37:47.299 --> 37:48.498
Really?

37:48.500 --> 37:50.333
Can you get someone here
by morning?

37:55.741 --> 37:58.541
Yes.
I think i can.

37:58.543 --> 38:00.710
Great!

38:00.712 --> 38:03.046
Okay, sweetheart.
It's bath time.

38:03.048 --> 38:05.682
Blanca, can you straighten up
in here

38:05.684 --> 38:06.783
While i start
katy's bath?

38:06.785 --> 38:09.486
Sure, mrs. Stappord.
[ gasps ] yay!

38:42.321 --> 38:45.689
Here we are.
Home, sweet home.

38:45.691 --> 38:47.490
Do you like it,
mama?

38:47.492 --> 38:50.460
Mm. I do.

38:50.462 --> 38:52.495
[ door closes ]

38:52.497 --> 38:53.997
It's very clean.

38:53.999 --> 38:56.566
Go play, buddy.
Let your mom get settled in.

38:56.568 --> 39:02.005
Are you, uh --
you impressed?

39:02.007 --> 39:05.508
I don't know.
Did you hire someone?

39:05.510 --> 39:07.410
No, i did not.

39:07.412 --> 39:10.513
Then i'm very impressed.

39:10.515 --> 39:13.683
You did good, mr. Spence.

39:13.685 --> 39:16.586
Thank you,
[spanish accent] mrs. Spence.

39:19.024 --> 39:21.958
Hey, where did zoila put
my hot wheels?

39:21.960 --> 39:24.361
Zoila?

39:24.363 --> 39:25.862
She came by
and gave me some pointers.

39:25.864 --> 39:27.997
Uh...
Check your toy chest.

39:27.999 --> 39:29.399
Wait a second.

39:30.902 --> 39:32.769
Did zoila clean
this whole apartment?

39:32.771 --> 39:34.371
No.

39:34.373 --> 39:36.039
Carmen helped, too.
Thanks, pal.

39:36.041 --> 39:41.077
Miguel,
go play in your room, hm?

39:46.017 --> 39:47.784
Okay, okay.

39:47.786 --> 39:49.486
[ sighs ]

39:49.488 --> 39:52.756
But before you say
anything...

39:52.758 --> 39:58.595
It's just --
[crying] it's been so hard.

39:58.597 --> 40:01.164
Knock it off!

40:01.166 --> 40:03.500
You made my friends
clean the apartment?

40:03.502 --> 40:05.735
No, they offered.
You should have said no!

40:05.737 --> 40:07.170
But i didn't hire anyone.
Isn't that what you wanted?

40:07.172 --> 40:10.039
What i wanted
was for you to grow up.

40:10.041 --> 40:12.642
And to take care of things
like an adult.

40:12.644 --> 40:15.011
Okay.

40:15.013 --> 40:17.514
You're right.
I made a mistake.

40:17.516 --> 40:20.083
When i was married
to ernesto,

40:20.085 --> 40:21.684
I knew
that i could count on him.

40:21.686 --> 40:23.520
You can count on me,
rosie.

40:23.522 --> 40:24.721
Then prove it!

40:24.723 --> 40:26.956
I will.
But listen, i'm not ernesto.

40:28.693 --> 40:31.661
It's not fair that you
keep comparing me to a dead man.

40:41.072 --> 40:42.806
Thank you.

40:42.808 --> 40:44.073
"pasaporte"?

40:44.075 --> 40:48.044
<i>Como no,</i> officer.
Here you go.

40:48.046 --> 40:49.579
Ernest falta...

40:49.581 --> 40:51.114
What's the purpose
of your visit to america?

40:51.116 --> 40:55.051
I'm here to see my wife.

